## Getting Started

This section will guide you through the initial setup and preparation for running the autonomous campus delivery robot.

### Hardware Prerequisites

Before starting, ensure you have:
- **HiWonder JetAuto Kit** or a robot with the following components:
  - LiDAR sensor
  - Motors
  - Computing unit (Jetson Nano or equivalent)
---
## Dependencies

- **ROS 1** (Robot Operating System) - Tested on ROS Noetic
- **Linux-based operating system** - Ubuntu 18.04 or later
- **Properly configured catkin workspace** for ROS development

---

## Installing

### Clone the Repository

Fork the code into your directory:

```bash
cd ~/your_workspace/src
git clone https://github.com/your-username/autonomous-campus-delivery-robot.git
cd autonomous-campus-delivery-robot
```

### Build the Workspace

```bash
cd ~/your_workspace
catkin_make
```

### Set up the ROS Environment
1. `catkin_make` in this folder

2. Export ROS_MASTER_URI=http://localhost:<Your Local Host>

3. Source the setup file:
```bash
source ~/your_workspace/devel/setup.sh
```

### Kill ROS Master (Important)

Before running any SLAM or navigation commands, always ensure ROS Master is not already running. Kill any existing ROS processes:

```bash
sudo lsof -i :<Your Local Host>
sudo kill -9 <PID>
sudo lsof -i :<Your Local Host>
```

Replace `<PID>` with the actual process ID shown. The last command should return empty, indicating ROS Master is stopped.

### Verify Installation

```bash
rospack find gmapping
rostopic list
```

---

## Executing Program

All functionality is controlled through the `launch.sh` script. Run the script to see all available options:

```bash
./launch.sh
```

### Available Commands

**1. gmap** - Launch SLAM (GMapping)
```bash
./launch.sh gmap
```
Starts the GMapping SLAM algorithm and RViz visualization. The robot begins scanning and building a map of the environment.

**2. save** - Save the Campus Map
```bash
./launch.sh save
```
Saves the currently built map to persistent storage (`.pgm` image file and `.yaml` configuration file).

**3. gnavi** - SLAM with Navigation
```bash
./launch.sh gnavi
```
Launches both GMapping SLAM and the navigation stack together. Enables autonomous navigation with the built map.

**4. delivery** - Delivery Phase
```bash
./launch.sh delivery
```
Launches the autonomous delivery navigation system using a pre-built campus map. The robot uses saved map for localization and path planning.

**5. full** - Complete Workflow
```bash
./launch.sh full
```
Runs the complete workflow automatically: launches GMapping SLAM and navigation, waits 20 seconds for initialization, then automatically transitions to delivery phase. Use this for end-to-end testing.

---

## Help

### Issue: ROS Master Already Running

If ROS Master is stuck on port <Your Local Host>:

```bash
sudo lsof -i :<Your Local Host>
sudo kill -9 <PID>
sudo lsof -i :<Your Local Host>
```

Then relaunch:

```bash
roslaunch jetauto_slam slam.launch slam_methods:=gmapping
```

### Issue: No Laser Scans Received

Check if LiDAR is connected:

```bash
lsusb | grep LIDAR
rostopic hz /scan
```

If permission issues:

```bash
sudo usermod -a -G dialout $USER
sudo reboot
```

